Input in Fortran can be read using read(*,*) n. Then initialize ans to 0. The formula in Java: ans += (long) i * ((long) n / (long) i) * (((long) n / (long) i) + 1) / 2;

In Fortran, the order of operations matters. Let's break it down. For each term:

term = i * (n / i) * ( (n / i) + 1 )
